    "3.4.2) can be used to refine these gaps.",
    "We caution however, that the HF method tends to overestimate band gaps, such that ∆ HF is often significantly larger than the experimentally extracted gaps.",
    "∆ HF may also be sensitive to the number of active bands included-central-band only calculations often lead to overestimates of the band gap compared ones that include more active bands.The Chern number and Berry curvature of a gapped HF state can be obtained using the numerical method outlined in Ref.",
